post_text: The USDA has extended the Free Lunch benefit for communities. Starting Tuesday, September 8, all children aged 18 and under can receive a free lunch at Momence schools. Lunches are available Monday through Thursday from 10 a.m. to 12 noon at Momence Junior High School east entrance and Jeneir Elementary school west entrance. Lunches may be picked up in a 5 pack any day Monday through Thursday (Except Monday, Sept. 7 which is a holiday.) Only one 5 pack per child. Parents may pick up lunches for their children. Guidelines state that we are not able to give out lunches to anyone other than the child or the parents (no neighbors or friends can pick up lunches for someone else).

Momence Families, our staff is missing our students and all the parents we are used to seeing. We've heard from many of you that you're feeling the same way. In honor of Staff Appreciation Week next week, we'd love to share your messages.

How can you join in? Take a picture holding a piece of paper with your written message. Students, families, colleagues- we can't wait to see all your faces. Send your pictures to lthrasher@mcusd1.net. Please send all pictures by Monday, May 4.

Thank you for helping us feel more connected during this time and for helping us celebrate our amazing MCUSD #1 staff.

post_text:
Last Friday the Governor announced that all in-person instruction for the remainder of this school year has ended. Although we are disappointed hearing this news because we now know our students will not be returning, we understand the reasoning behind the decision. With that, we are now releasing our May Remote Learning Calendar. Please note that this district calendar is not all inclusive; there may be additional dates specific to each building. Please watch for additional information that may be provided by each building.
We know that you may have additional questions. Please know, our planning is on-going, and we will continue to provide information as it becomes available. Thanks for your continued support during this crisis.

MCHS SENIORS:
Final Reminder From Jostens:
Jostens is planning a drive-thru cap and gown delivery event for Monday, April 20, starting at 12:00pm until 2:00pm. The Drive-Thru Location will be at the south end of Momence Community High School by the cafeteria. There will be no need to enter the building. There is a flyer attached with instructions for you to follow.
Students still needing to place a cap & gown or tassel order, can place their order at www.GetGradStuff.com . *If you order by Sunday, we will be able to deliver it on Monday. No new orders can be placed at the delivery event. All balances due will need to be paid prior to the event. No payments can be taken at the delivery event.
Please let Jostens know if you have any questions or if there is anything further you need from us at LisleOffice@jostens.com. We look forward to seeing the students and delivering their caps and gowns and graduation items.

post_text:
For those of you responding to help us with PPE, thank you! We received some great information from one of our local healthcare providers about PPE, and how to care for it. We also received help from our local health department. Because of this, we do not need any additional PPE at this time.
While we will continue to provide PPE for our staff, any excess we have will be taken to our local hospitals or our health department to be distributed to our healthcare providers. Thanks so much for your help, and, thanks for supporting our healthcare providers!

post_text:
National School Bus Safety Week is the perfect time to talk to your child about school bus safety. Tell your child that when getting on and off the bus to always watch for oncoming traffic. While at the bus stop, they should stand at least three giant steps away from the approaching bus. The observance is also a time for motorists to learn and adhere to all the bus stopping laws.

To spread awareness about school bus safety, share #NationalSchoolBusSafetyWeek or #NSBSW on social media.

River Valley FFA Brat Sale:
The River Valley FFA Annual Brat Sale will be held on Saturday, October 19th, 2019 10am-2pm. Buy your brats from our MCHS FFA members at the EARL D. Schoeffner Farm Museum at 122 N Dixie Hwy., Momence, IL. AND at the Grant Park Co-op Grain Co. at 116 S. Main St., Grant Park, IL.. For a low price of $5.00, you will get 1 brat, chips, cookie, and drink; or for $7.00, you will get 2 brats, chips, cookie, and drink.

ATTENTION JE-NEIR PARENTS:
The Yankee Candle fundraiser is due NO LATER than Friday, October 18th. Historically we have been able to accept late orders, however, this year we will not be able to accept any orders after the 18th in order to ensure our delivery arrives before Thanksgiving Break. ***This applies to paper orders ONLY.

In addition, if you have your orders complete, please send them in with your student.

If you have any questions, please call the office at 815-472-6646.

Thank you!

post_text: It is that time of year again! Redskin Nation and our MCHS athletes are selling "Affy Tapples" to raise money. Please see one of our high school athletes to order yours today! The choices are: Original-no nuts, Original-with nuts, Original-with sprinkles. They are just $2.00 an apple so they make an inexpensive and delicious way to help keep funding going! Cases of 24 are also available at a discounted price of $40. The athletes must have their orders and payments turned in by October 8th in order for the October 17th delivery, so hurry and order yours today! If you cannot find an athlete, contact the high school office at (815) 472-6477.
